config: Increase BUILD_MAX_HIGHTABLE from 16MB to 80MB for large ramdisk support

The BUILD_MAX_HIGHTABLE constant defines the maximum space that can be reserved
in high-memory (ZoneHigh) for runtime tables and buffers. The current 16MB limit
is sufficient for standard SeaBIOS operation but is inadequate to support
custom-sized ramdisks as large as 63MB, the code for which is being added.

A single ramdisk can be as large as 63 MB (2 heads * 1024 cylinders * 63 sectors
per track * 512 bytes sector size). The ramdisk shared buffer must be allocated
in ZoneHigh to persist across the boot process. Only one ramdisk is loaded at a
time, its buffer must accommodate the full image. Raising BUILD_MAX_HIGHTABLE to
80MB provides headroom for a 63MB ramdisk plus additional runtime allocations,
while remaining well within typical system RAM limits on modern hardware.

Signed-off-by: Mike Banon <mikebdp2@gmail.com>
---
 src/config.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/config.h b/src/config.h
index 5700450a..91370684 100644
--- a/src/config.h
+++ b/src/config.h
@@ -18,7 +18,7 @@
 #define BUILD_MAX_E820 128
 // Space to reserve in high-memory for tables
 #define BUILD_MIN_HIGHTABLE (256*1024)
-#define BUILD_MAX_HIGHTABLE (16*1024*1024)
+#define BUILD_MAX_HIGHTABLE (80*1024*1024)
 // Largest supported externaly facing drive id
 #define BUILD_MAX_EXTDRIVE 36
 // Number of bytes the smbios may be and still live in the f-segment
